An 18-year-old, Oladoyin Taiwo, has been remanded in prison by an Osun State Magistrate Court, Ile Ife for allegedly stealing 12 yards of Ankara cloth inside a police station. The prosecutor, Inspector Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that TaiwoÂ committed the offence on May 15, 2020 in Ile-Ife, by breaking into the office of Inspector Vitowanu Bukola through the door and stealing N4,000, a standing fan, a quarter bag of rice, GOTV antenna, one DVD players and a socket, among others.